<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-895-238  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 895 238.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Nov 20 1989 v6 n46 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MFS contests telcos' lock on local loop. (Metropolitan FiberSystems Inc. files Federal Communications Commission, Departmentof Justice petitions)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Taff, Anita.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Metropolitan Fiber Systems Inc (MFS) files two petitions askingthe FCC and the US Department of Justice to open up local switchedtelephone service to competition.andP;  If granted, the petitions willhave succeeded in ending the regional Bell holding companies'(RBHCs') virtual monopoly on local switched services.andP;  Currently,most states only allow competition in the area of private-lineservices.andP;  The MFS petitions specifically ask the JusticeDepartment and the FCC to begin a proceeding forcing RBHCs acrossthe country to interconnect with and allow collocation of MSFequipment in central offices and to unbundle access tariffs sothat MFS can purchase solely the components it needs.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Metropolitan Fiber Systems Inc. (cases).andO;Topic:     Court CasesUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionTelephone CompaniesLocal CommunicationBell Regional Holding CompaniesMonopoliesUnited States. Department of Justice.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>